{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "00-title",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Experiment 2 — Run Comparison: Pre-Fix (Old) vs Post-Fix (New)\n",
    "\n",
    "Side-by-side technical and results comparison of the two complete Exp2 full runs.\n",
    "\n",
    "| | Old Run (`run2_backup`) | New Run (`results/`) |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| **RR Judge prompt** | Direct score, ~50 tok output | Chain-of-thought, ~300 tok output |\n",
    "| **Token budget** | Fixed 1,000 for all profiles | Scaled 1,000–1,600 (Fix A) |\n",
    "| **Style directives** | Replacement framing ("MUST include") | Additive framing ("ADDITIONALLY...") (Fix B) |\n",
    "| **Factual anchor** | None | STEP 0 factual foundation injected (Fix C) |\n",
    "| **Gold chunk dataset** | `sampled_questions.json` (some 1–2 gold chunks) | `filtered_questions.json` (≥3 gold chunks) |\n",
    "| **`retrieved_chunks`** | Not stored in session JSONL | Full chunk dicts stored (Fix D) |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "01-config",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import json, warnings\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.patches as mpatches\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from scipy import stats\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "BASE = Path('results')\n",
    "OLD_DIR  = BASE / 'run2_backup'\n",
    "NEW_DIR  = BASE\n",
    "\n",
    "OLD_CSV  = OLD_DIR / 'exp2_session_metrics.csv'\n",
    "NEW_CSV  = NEW_DIR / 'exp2_session_metrics.csv'\n",
    "OLD_JSON = OLD_DIR / 'exp2_results_summary.json'\n",
    "NEW_JSON = NEW_DIR / 'exp2_results_summary.json'\n",
    "FIG_DIR  = BASE / 'figures_comparison'\n",
    "FIG_DIR.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Palette ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "C_R0  = '#5B8DB8'   # blue  — baseline\n",
    "C_R1  = '#E87C4E'   # orange — personalized\n",
    "C_OLD = '#9B59B6'   # purple — old run\n",
    "C_NEW = '#27AE60'   # green  — new run\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Paths OK:', OLD_CSV.exists(), NEW_CSV.exists(), OLD_JSON.exists(), NEW_JSON.exists())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "02-load",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Load CSVs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "old_df = pd.read_csv(OLD_CSV)\n",
    "new_df = pd.read_csv(NEW_CSV)\n",
    "\n",
    "with open(OLD_JSON) as f: old_summary = json.load(f)\n",
    "with open(NEW_JSON) as f: new_summary = json.load(f)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Old run: {len(old_df):,} sessions | New run: {len(new_df):,} sessions')\n",
    "print(f'Old columns: {list(old_df.columns)}')\n",
    "print(f'New columns: {list(new_df.columns)}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "03-md-headline",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Table 1 — Headline Metric Comparison\n",
    "\n",
    "All metrics shown as R1−R0 lift (Δ). Cohen's d and significance from paired Wilcoxon tests."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "04-headline-table",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "METRICS = ['SCS', 'RR', 'CR@5', 'CR@10', 'ER', 'Eng']\n",
    "METRIC_LABELS = {'SCS': 'Style Conformance (SCS)', 'RR': 'Response Relevance (RR)',\n",
    "                 'CR@5': 'Chunk Recall@5', 'CR@10': 'Chunk Recall@10',\n",
    "                 'ER': 'Essential Recall (ER)', 'Eng': 'Engagement'}\n",
    "\n",
    "rows = []\n",
    "for m in METRICS:\n",
    "    o = old_summary['significance'][m]\n",
    "    n = new_summary['significance'][m]\n",
    "    rows.append({\n",
    "        'Metric': METRIC_LABELS[m],\n",
    "        'Old Δ': f\"{o['mean_diff']:+.4f}\",\n",
    "        'Old d': f\"{o['cohens_d']:+.3f}\",\n",
    "        'Old p': f\"{o['p_value']:.2e}\",\n",
    "        'Old sig': '✓' if o['significant'] else '✗',\n",
    "        'New Δ': f\"{n['mean_diff']:+.4f}\",\n",
    "        'New d': f\"{n['cohens_d']:+.3f}\",\n",
    "        'New p': f\"{n['p_value']:.2e}\",\n",
    "        'New sig': '✓' if n['significant'] else '✗',\n",
    "        'Δ change': f\"{n['mean_diff'] - o['mean_diff']:+.4f}\",\n",
    "    })\n",
    "\n",
    "tbl = pd.DataFrame(rows).set_index('Metric')\n",
    "\n",
    "def highlight_rr(df):\n",
    "    style = pd.DataFrame('', index=df.index, columns=df.columns)\n",
    "    for col in df.columns:\n",
    "        if 'Old' in col:\n",
    "            style[col] = style[col].where(df.index != 'Response Relevance (RR)', 'background-color: #ffe0e0')\n",
    "        if 'New' in col:\n",
    "            style[col] = style[col].where(df.index != 'Response Relevance (RR)', 'background-color: #e0ffe0')\n",
    "    return style\n",
    "\n",
    "print('=== Headline Metric Comparison (R1 − R0 lift) ===')\n",
    "display(tbl.style.apply(highlight_rr, axis=None))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "05-md-fig1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Fig 1 — Metric Lift Comparison (Δ = R1 − R0)\n",
    "\n",
    "Grouped bar chart: old vs new run for each metric's R1−R0 lift. Highlights whether fixes preserved, improved or slightly reduced each metric."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "06-fig1-lift-bars",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "old_deltas = [old_summary['significance'][m]['mean_diff'] for m in METRICS]\n",
    "new_deltas = [new_summary['significance'][m]['mean_diff'] for m in METRICS]\n",
    "old_sigs   = [old_summary['significance'][m]['significant'] for m in METRICS]\n",
    "new_sigs   = [new_summary['significance'][m]['significant'] for m in METRICS]\n",
    "\n",
    "x     = np.arange(len(METRICS))\n",
    "width = 0.35\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 5))\n",
    "bars_old = ax.bar(x - width/2, old_deltas, width, color=C_OLD, alpha=0.85, label='Old run (pre-fix)')\n",
    "bars_new = ax.bar(x + width/2, new_deltas, width, color=C_NEW, alpha=0.85, label='New run (post-fix)')\n",
    "\n",
    "# significance markers\n",
    "for i, (b, sig) in enumerate(zip(bars_old, old_sigs)):\n",
    "    if sig:\n",
    "        ax.text(b.get_x() + b.get_width()/2, b.get_height() + 0.003, '*',\n",
    "                ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=12, color='black')\n",
    "for i, (b, sig) in enumerate(zip(bars_new, new_sigs)):\n",
    "    if sig:\n",
    "        ax.text(b.get_x() + b.get_width()/2, b.get_height() + 0.003, '*',\n",
    "                ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=12, color='black')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.axhline(0, color='black', linewidth=0.8, linestyle='--')\n",
    "ax.set_xticks(x)\n",
    "ax.set_xticklabels([METRIC_LABELS[m] for m in METRICS], rotation=20, ha='right', fontsize=10)\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('R1 − R0 Lift (Δ mean)', fontsize=11)\n",
    "ax.set_title('Fig 1 — R1 vs R0 Metric Lift: Old vs New Run\\n* = statistically significant (Wilcoxon p < 0.05)', fontsize=12)\n",
    "ax.legend(fontsize=10)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Annotate RR bar with labels\n",
    "rr_idx = METRICS.index('RR')\n",
    "ax.annotate('RR inverted!', xy=(x[rr_idx] - width/2, old_deltas[rr_idx] - 0.01),\n",
    "            xytext=(x[rr_idx] - width/2 - 0.8, old_deltas[rr_idx] - 0.1),\n",
    "            arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', color='red'), color='red', fontsize=9)\n",
    "ax.annotate('Resolved', xy=(x[rr_idx] + width/2, new_deltas[rr_idx] + 0.005),\n",
    "            xytext=(x[rr_idx] + width/2 + 0.3, 0.05),\n",
    "            arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', color='green'), color='green', fontsize=9)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(FIG_DIR / 'fig1_lift_comparison.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "07-md-fig2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Fig 2 — RR Score Distribution: Old vs New Run\n",
    "\n",
    "Shows how the RR score distribution shifted between runs. Old run: R1 clearly below R0 (inversion). New run: R0 and R1 overlap."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "08-fig2-rr-dist",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Check available RR columns\n",
    "rr_col = 'rr' if 'rr' in old_df.columns else 'RR'\n",
    "print(f'RR column: {rr_col}')\n",
    "print('Old df columns:', list(old_df.columns))\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(13, 5), sharey=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "for ax, df, title, run_label in [\n",
    "    (axes[0], old_df, 'Old Run (pre-fix) — RR Inverted', 'Old'),\n",
    "    (axes[1], new_df, 'New Run (post-fix) — RR Inversion Resolved', 'New'),\n",
    "]:\n",
    "    col = 'rr' if 'rr' in df.columns else ('RR' if 'RR' in df.columns else None)\n",
    "    if col is None:\n",
    "        ax.text(0.5, 0.5, 'RR not in CSV', ha='center', va='center', transform=ax.transAxes)\n",
    "        continue\n",
    "    for mode, color, lbl in [('R0', C_R0, 'R0 Generic'), ('R1', C_R1, 'R1 Personalized')]:\n",
    "        sub = df[df['mode'] == mode][col].dropna()\n",
    "        ax.hist(sub, bins=20, alpha=0.6, color=color, label=f'{lbl} (μ={sub.mean():.3f})', density=True)\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel('RR Score (1–5)', fontsize=10)\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel('Density', fontsize=10)\n",
    "    ax.set_title(title, fontsize=10)\n",
    "    ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
    "    ax.axvline(df[df['mode']=='R0'][col].mean(), color=C_R0, linestyle='--', linewidth=1.5)\n",
    "    ax.axvline(df[df['mode']=='R1'][col].mean(), color=C_R1, linestyle='--', linewidth=1.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig.suptitle('Fig 2 — RR Score Distribution: Old vs New Run', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(FIG_DIR / 'fig2_rr_distribution.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "09-md-fig3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Fig 3 — Engagement Score Distribution: Old vs New Run\n",
    "\n",
    "The new run uses the same engagement scoring mechanism but with different R1 responses (factual anchor + additive directives). Shows whether engagement quality changed."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "10-fig3-eng-dist",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "eng_col = 'engagement_score' if 'engagement_score' in old_df.columns else 'engagement'\n",
    "print('Engagement column:', eng_col)\n",
