   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "15-md-fig6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Fig 6 — Dual-Axis Tradeoff: SCS Δ vs RR Δ vs Engagement Δ\n",
    "\n",
    "Summary of the core tradeoff. The old run maximised SCS/Engagement but broke RR. The new run keeps SCS/Engagement gains while restoring RR parity."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "16-fig6-tradeoff",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "summary_data = {\n",
    "    'Old Run\\n(pre-fix)': {\n",
    "        'SCS Δ':  old_summary['significance']['SCS']['mean_diff'],\n",
    "        'RR Δ':   old_summary['significance']['RR']['mean_diff'],\n",
    "        'Eng Δ':  old_summary['significance']['Eng']['mean_diff'],\n",
    "        'CR@5 Δ': old_summary['significance']['CR@5']['mean_diff'],\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    'New Run\\n(post-fix)': {\n",
    "        'SCS Δ':  new_summary['significance']['SCS']['mean_diff'],\n",
    "        'RR Δ':   new_summary['significance']['RR']['mean_diff'],\n",
    "        'Eng Δ':  new_summary['significance']['Eng']['mean_diff'],\n",
    "        'CR@5 Δ': new_summary['significance']['CR@5']['mean_diff'],\n",
    "    },\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "metric_keys = ['SCS Δ', 'RR Δ', 'Eng Δ', 'CR@5 Δ']\n",
    "colors_runs = [C_OLD, C_NEW]\n",
    "run_labels  = list(summary_data.keys())\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(9, 5))\n",
    "x = np.arange(len(metric_keys))\n",
    "w = 0.35\n",
    "for i, (run, color) in enumerate(zip(run_labels, colors_runs)):\n",
    "    vals = [summary_data[run][k] for k in metric_keys]\n",
    "    bars = ax.bar(x + (i - 0.5) * w, vals, w, color=color, alpha=0.85, label=run.replace('\\n', ' '))\n",
    "    for b, v in zip(bars, vals):\n",
    "        ax.text(b.get_x() + b.get_width()/2,\n",
    "                b.get_height() + (0.005 if v >= 0 else -0.015),\n",
    "                f'{v:+.3f}', ha='center', va='bottom' if v >= 0 else 'top', fontsize=8)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.axhline(0, color='black', linewidth=0.8, linestyle='--')\n",
    "ax.set_xticks(x)\n",
    "ax.set_xticklabels(metric_keys, fontsize=11)\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('R1 − R0 Lift (Δ mean)', fontsize=11)\n",
    "ax.set_title('Fig 6 — Tradeoff Summary: Old vs New Run (R1−R0 Lift)', fontsize=12)\n",
    "ax.legend(fontsize=10)\n",
    "\n",
    "# shade RR column\n",
    "rr_x = metric_keys.index('RR Δ')\n",
    "ax.axvspan(rr_x - 0.5, rr_x + 0.5, alpha=0.08, color='red')\n",
    "ax.text(rr_x, ax.get_ylim()[0] * 0.9, 'RR\\n(critical)', ha='center', fontsize=8, color='red')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(FIG_DIR / 'fig6_tradeoff_summary.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "17-md-fig7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Fig 7 — Absolute Score Comparison: R0 and R1 Means\n",
    "\n",
    "Scatter shows where each run's R0 and R1 means land for RR and Engagement (the two most thesis-relevant dimensions)."
   ]
  },
