   "source": [
    "## Technical Changes Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "### Root Cause of RR Inversion (Old Run)\n",
    "R1 style directives were **replacement framing**: \"MUST include ASCII diagrams\", \"MUST use numbered steps\". With a fixed 1,000-token budget, LLMs fulfilled style requirements at the expense of factual content. Result: R1 responses were stylistically formatted but factually incomplete → lower RR scores than R0.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Fix A — Profile-Aware Token Budget (`tutor_agent.py`)\n",
    "```python\n",
    "def _get_max_tokens(self, reasoning_plan):\n",
    "    if reasoning_plan is None:\n",
    "        return 1000  # R0 baseline unchanged\n",
    "    structural_dims = sum([\n",
    "        vector.get('vis_ver') == -1,   # Visual\n",
    "        vector.get('seq_glo') == -1,   # Sequential\n",
    "        vector.get('act_ref') == -1,   # Active\n",
    "    ])\n",
    "    return min(1000 + structural_dims * 200, 1600)\n",
    "```\n",
    "Structural profiles (Visual/Sequential/Active) get up to +600 tokens. R0 baseline unchanged.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Fix B — Additive Directive Framing (`profile_agent.py`)\n",
    "| Old | New |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| `\"MUST include ASCII diagram\"` | `\"First provide complete explanation. Then ADDITIONALLY include ASCII diagram...\"` |\n",
    "| `\"Use numbered steps ONLY\"` | `\"Each step must contain FULL explanation — do not abbreviate factual content\"` |\n",
    "| `\"Add hands-on exercise\"` | `\"Provide complete factual explanation first. At END, ADDITIONALLY add exercise...\"` |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Fix C — Factual Anchor Injection (`profile_agent.py`)\n",
    "```python\n",
    "_CONTENT_ANCHOR = (\n",
    "    \"## STEP 0 — FACTUAL FOUNDATION (always do this first)\\n\"\n",
    "    \"Before applying any style formatting, write 2–3 sentences that directly \"\n",
    "    \"answer the question using the key facts from the retrieved evidence.\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "```\n",
    "Injected at the top of every R1 system prompt, before style directives.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Fix D — `retrieved_chunks` field (`tutor_agent.py`)\n",
    "Full chunk dicts (text + heading) now stored in session JSONL, enabling post-hoc retrieval quality analysis without re-querying FAISS.\n",
    "\n",
    "### RR Judge Prompt Overhaul (`judge_prompts.py`)\n",
    "Old: direct 1–5 score, ~50 output tokens.  \n",
    "New: chain-of-thought — extract gold claims → check presence → score, ~300 output tokens.  \n",
    "Trade-off: more reliable, interpretable scores; ~50% higher eval cost per call."
   ]
